	a dprr:SecondarySource ;
	dprr:hasName "The Magistrates of the Roman Republic, Vol. I" ;
	dprr:hasBiblio "Broughton, T. R. S., The Magistrates of the Roman Republic, Vol. I. Published by the American Philological Association. New York 1952." ;
	dprr:hasAbbreviation "Broughton MRR I" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3334> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3334" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Lucilius, 56 and 69, 60, 62 M; cf. Cichorius, Untersuch. Lucil. 244-248. They may have served under Mucius Scaevola in Asia." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3333> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3333" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Lucilius, 56 and 69, 60, 62 M; cf. Cichorius, Untersuch. Lucil. 244-248. They may have served under Mucius Scaevola in Asia." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3332> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3332" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cichorius supposes from the part given these men in Lucilius' account of Scaevola's defence that they were members of his staff, though their offices are not identifiable. On Nomentanus, note that Cichorius' emendation of Lucilius 56 and 69 M is accepted by Warmington, and the identification of the person by Kubitschek (SBAW 167.6.64) and Münzer (RE s. v. \"Nomentanus.\"). On Hortensius, see 111, Praetors and note 3." .
